Always use variables from style.css. Never use hard-coded values.

All theme changes (dark/light) must be done by swapping CSS variables.

always make sure there is contrast when changing the theme

No inline styles

No hard-coded fallback colors

Do not create duplicate classes or duplicate media queries.

Always do text-align: left on mobile screens

Use the following breakpoints:

Large screens: @media (min-width: 2560px)

Other breakpoints:

@media (max-width: 1440px)

@media (max-width: 768px)

@media (max-width: 425px)

Ensure all responsive styles are organized under these breakpoints.

Component Structure Rules

Always follow these rules when generating or modifying code.

Never ignore or override these rules unless the user explicitly asks.